\begin_layout Standard
The above axioms describe a mathematical idealization involving infinitely
 precise measurements.
 In an actual experimental setup with an ensemble of quantum states that
 are not exactly identically prepared, and with small imperfections and
 inaccuracies in measuring devices, an experimenter might only be able to
 determine that the probability of the event 
\begin_inset Formula $\proj{0}$
\end_inset

